Can a svelte file have more than one script section if tagged as a module like below?  I saw this code in a UI component example.

<script lang="ts" context="module">
  import { z } from "zod";
  export const formSchema = z.object({
    username: z.string().min(2).max(50)
  });
  export type FormSchema = typeof formSchema;
</script>

No, a Svelte file cannot have more than one `<script>` tag with `context="module"`. In Svelte, you can have multiple `<script>` tags, but only one of them can be a module context script. The `context="module"` script runs once when the module is evaluated (which is typically when the app or page loads), and it's used for module-level code, such as imports, exports, and other setup that isn't directly tied to a single component instance.

The code you provided is a correct use of the module context script. It's importing a library and defining an exportable schema, which is exactly the kind of thing `context="module"` is designed for. This script will run once, regardless of how many times the component is instantiated.

If you need to separate concerns within a single module script for readability or organization, you can simply use comments or separate the code into distinct sections within the same `<script>` tag. For instance:

```svelte
<script lang="ts" context="module">
  // Imports
  import { z } from "zod";

  // Schema definition
  export const formSchema = z.object({
    username: z.string().min(2).max(50)
  });

  // Type export
  export type FormSchema = typeof formSchema;

  // Other module-level code can go here
</script>
```

Remember, anything that needs to be reactive or tied to the component's instance should go in a regular `<script>` tag without `context="module"`.

