4. **Setting PageState**: When you use `pushState` or `replaceState` in your Svelte components, you can now include `bottlePreLoad` data as part of the state object.

Remember that extending the `PageState` interface in this way makes the additional properties available globally. This means any page in your application can potentially access these properties, though they may be undefined if not set for that particular route. This approach provides a consistent way to handle state across different parts of your application.

