    <button type="button" on:click={() => downloadCSV(data.form.exportString, 'bottles.csv')}>
        Download CSV
    </button>
</Form.Root>
```

In this implementation:
- The `downloadCSV` function creates a Blob from the CSV data, generates a temporary URL, and uses an invisible anchor (`<a>`) element to trigger the download.
- The filename 'bottles.csv' is used as the default name for the downloaded file.
- The button is of type `button` (not `submit`) to ensure it doesn't submit the form when clicked.

This approach should work well for your use case and provide users with an easy way to download their bottle listings.

