To read the contents of a file uploaded via your `FileButton` component and set the contents to your `importString` in the form, you can use the `FileReader` API provided by JavaScript. This API allows you to read the contents of files (or raw data buffers) stored in a `FileList` object, like the one you have from the file input.

Here's how you can implement the `onChangeHandler` function to read the file and set its contents to `$form.importString`:

1. Check if any files are selected.
2. Create a new `FileReader` instance.
3. Add an `onload` event handler to the FileReader to handle the file content once it is loaded.
4. Read the content of the file using `readAsText`.
5. Set the read content to `$form.importString`.

Here's an implementation example:

```javascript
// Script section of your +page.svelte
function onChangeHandler(e: Event): void {
    if (files.length === 0) {
        return; // No file selected
    }

    const file = files[0]; // Assuming you're only handling the first file
    const reader = new FileReader();

    reader.onload = function (event) {
        const fileContent = event.target.result;
        if (typeof fileContent === "string") {
            // Set the read content to $form.importString
            $form.importString = fileContent;
        }
    };

    reader.readAsText(file); // Read the content of the file
}
```

